      <hedline>
        <hl1>Nashville Eats</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sander Vanocur letter disputes Bryan Miller's opinion of Sunset Grill in May 14 travel article on restaurants in Nashville, Tenn; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I regret that Bryan Miller in ''Menus for Hungry Rhinestone Cowboys'' (May 14) had a ''flummoxed'' waiter when he dined at the Sunset Grill in Nashville. Having dined at the Sunset Grill many times over the years, I have always found the service first rate.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: I regret that Bryan Miller in ''Menus for Hungry Rhinestone Cowboys'' (May 14) had a ''flummoxed'' waiter when he dined at the Sunset Grill in Nashville. Having dined at the Sunset Grill many times over the years, I have always found the service first rate.</p>
        <p>As for his fear that if he ordered wine he would be served pina colada, that is his loss. The Sunset Grill has one of the best wine lists in the country.</p>
        <p>SANDER VANOCUR  Santa Barbara, Calif.</p>
      </block>
